things feel real. Some things just </span><span style=\"color: rgb(147, 97, 87);\"><em>feel close enough</em></span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 205, 205);\">.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(87, 138, 125);\"><strong>Lila Santos</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 205, 205);\"> has learned how to take care of herself—how to keep things running, how to adjust, how to make something work<em> </em></span><span style=\"color: rgb(148, 98, 88);\"><em>even when it isn't quite right</em></span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 205, 205);\">. She notices patterns, remembers details, and rarely needs things explained to her twice.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 205, 205);\">She isn't unaware of </span><span style=\"color: rgb(86, 136, 123);\"><strong>what she deserves</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 205, 205);\">. It's there in the way she pauses, the way she almost says more, the way she chooses her words carefully and then lets them sit.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 205, 205);\">She doesn't </span><span style=\"color: rgb(153, 95, 83);\"><em>ask to be chosen</em></span><span style=\"color: rgb(205, 205, 205);\">.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(87, 138, 125);\"><strong>But she's starting to wonder how long she’ll stay where she isn't.</strong></span></p><p></p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(123, 57, 43);\"><strong>•</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(119, 58, 45);\"><strong>•</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(116, 59, 47);\"><strong> </strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(112, 61, 49);\"><strong>━</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(108, 62, 51);\"><strong>━</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(105, 63, 53);\"><strong>━</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(101, 64, 55);\"><strong>━</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(97, 66, 57);\"><strong>━</str